article.headline: Penn St. 66, Colgate 48
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Geary Claxton scored 14 points and Jamelle Cornley added 12 as Penn State beat Colgate 66-48 on Sunday. Cornley, a career double-figure scorer, had scored more than 11 points in just two games this season, added eight rebounds as the Nittany Lions (7-4) improved to 7-0 at home. Kendall Chones scored 9 points for Colgate (6-5), which shot 35 percent from the field. The Raiders closed to within five points on two occasions in the second half, but Claxton made a pair of free throws and a finger-roll layup to give Penn State a 48-34 lead with 9:35 remaining. A wide-open 3-pointer from freshman Jeff Brooks gave Penn State its largest lead, 63-43, with 2:14 left. Claxton and Cornley scored all 11 points as Penn State opened up an 11-4 lead in the first five minutes. Cornley's elbow jumper with six minutes left in the first half gave Penn State a 27-11 lead, but the Nittany Lions would score just three points the rest of the half and led 30-20 at the break.
